le=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ush1665702873697.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ush1665702873697.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ush1665702873697.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ush1665702873697\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n               \n Glyphs \n      \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ush1665702873697__glyphs_89779\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Glyphs are images in a Uniface-proprietary format, which can be used as background images in forms, entities and application shells, and as icons in widgets, panel buttons, menus, and drag-and-drop formats.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ush1665702873697__p_d27185e1_d27186e1_d27187e1\">Glyphs are not usable in web or mobile applications.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ush1665702873697__p_d27188e1_d27189e1_d27190e1\">The glyph format is similar to a Microsoft Windows bitmap file (<span class=\"ph filepath\">.bmp</span>), but it is OS-independent and DBMS-independent.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ush1665702873697__p_d27191e1_d27192e1_d27193e1\">When defining a glyph, you can use any supported image format as your source image. Uniface contains a large range of image filters, which enable you to load image files irrespective of their format.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ush1665702873697__p_d27194e1_d27195e1_d27196e1\">For each glyph, you can also define a secondary image, which is used as a shadow during drag and drop operations. The secondary image must be exactly the same size as the primary image, and the black pixels must correspond to the white pixels in the primary image.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qsj1704711355836.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Image Handling</a><p>Uniface can display and print pictures that are stored as image files on disk, as glyphs, or BLOBs in a database. The type of picture can affect performance.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yoi1665702919920.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Glyphs</a><p>Uniface delivers a set of glyphs for use in its own tools and editors. New glyphs are added in each new version of Uniface, sometimes replacing older glyphs, sometimes as additions.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532823\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532823\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Glyphs Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Glyphs Glyphs are images in a Uniface-proprietary format, which can be used as background images in forms, entities and application shells, and as icons in widgets, panel buttons, menus, and drag-and-drop formats. Glyphs are not usable in web or mobile applications. The glyph format is similar to a Microsoft Windows bitmap file ( .bmp ), but it is OS-independent and DBMS-independent. When defining a glyph, you can use any supported image format as your source image. Uniface contains a large range of image filters, which enable you to load image files irrespective of their format. For each glyph, you can also define a secondary image, which is used as a shadow during drag and drop operations. The secondary image must be exactly the same size as the primary image, and the black pixels must correspond to the white pixels in the primary image. Related Links Image Handling Uniface can display and print pictures that are stored as image files on disk, as glyphs, or BLOBs in a database. The type of picture can affect performance. Uniface Glyphs Uniface delivers a set of glyphs for use in its own tools and editors. New glyphs are added in each new version of Uniface, sometimes replacing older glyphs, sometimes as additions. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}